sollya
------------------------------------------
Sollya is a tool environment for safe floating-point code development. It is
particularily targeted to the automatized implementation of libms. Amongst
other features, it offers a certified infinite norm and a fast Remez algorithm.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libfplll7-5.4.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libgmp10-6.2.1-2
  libmpfi0-1.5.4-1bl2
  libmpfr6-4.1.0-2
  libsollya-devel-8.0-1bl1
  libsollya8-8.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libxml2-2.9.12-2
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  bison-3.8.2-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  flex-2.6.4-2
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libfplll-devel-5.4.1-1bl1
  libgmp-devel-6.2.1-2
  libmpfi-devel-1.5.4-1bl2
  libmpfr-devel-4.1.0-2
  libprotobuf-devel-3.19.3-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.12-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.sollya.org/

Canonical download:
  https://www.sollya.org/releases/sollya-8.0/sollya-8.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack sollya-8.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./sollya-8.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sollya-8.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/sollya-8.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsollya8-8.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsollya-devel-8.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(sollya)
  /usr/bin/sollya.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sollya.README
  /usr/share/doc/sollya/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/sollya/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/sollya/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/sollya/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/sollya/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/sollya.1.gz

(libsollya8)
  /usr/bin/cygsollya-8.dll

(libsollya-devel)
  /usr/include/sollya-messages.h
  /usr/include/sollya.h
  /usr/lib/libsollya.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/sollya.pc

